<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-426-453  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 426 453.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC World  Oct 1990 v8 n10 p241(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Words into print. (tips on setting up custom WordPerfect and Word5.0 dictionaries) (includes related articles on WordPerfect 5.0and 5.1 password macros and customizing Word's spellingdictionary) (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Campbell, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Supplemental dictionaries can be created in WordPerfect and theycan be edited, merged or split like any other file.andP;  Press the F7function key, type a list of words with one word per line and thensave the file with a SUP extension.andP;  To use the supplementaldictionary, press the control key and the F2 function key and typein the dictionary file name.andP;  Add new words to the dictionary bypressing 3 when an unknown word comes up.andP;  In Word 5.0 thespelling checker must be run to create or add words to a userdictionary.andP;  Type a list of words and then press the Alt key andthe F6 function key to start the spell checker.andP;  Press 0 at thefirst unknown word and enter the dictionary's path and file name.andO;Type au for add user to add a word.andP;  Select exit when finished.andO;More tips are described in detail.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   WordPerfect (Word processing software) (programming)Microsoft Word 5.0 (Word processing software) (programming).andO;Topic:     Word ProcessingTutorialDictionariesSoftware Modification.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Spell-checking for special occasions. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>